==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enodation
<hw>En`o*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enodatio</ets> explanation, fr. <ets>enodare</ets> to free from
knots. See <er>Enode</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or operation of clearing
of knots, or of untying; hence, also, the solution of a
difficulty.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

